{"comments":"Bounded numeric primitives - the foundation of the ontology.\n\nEvery value in the design system has semantic meaning AND valid bounds.\nA hue is 0-359. A saturation is 0-100. A channel is 0-255. These are\nnot interchangeable, and the type system enforces this.\n\n## Design Philosophy\n\nWe do NOT use phantom types or type-level naturals here. Instead:\n- Each domain gets its own newtype (Hue, Saturation, Channel, etc.)\n- Smart constructors clamp or validate at construction time\n- The `Bounds` record documents valid ranges for serialization/UI\n\nThis keeps the types simple, serializable, and comprehensible to both\nhumans and AI agents consuming the schema.\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[123,11],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[123,3]},"title":"Clamps"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[124,10],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[124,3]},"title":"Wraps"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[125,11],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[125,3]},"title":"Finite"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Bounded"],"BoundsBehavior"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[127,54],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[127,1]},"title":"eqBoundsBehavior"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Bounded"],"BoundsBehavior"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[128,56],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[128,1]},"title":"ordBoundsBehavior"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Bounded"],"BoundsBehavior"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[133,25],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[130,1]},"title":"showBoundsBehavior"}],"comments":"How a bounded value behaves at its limits.\n\n## Behaviors\n\n- `Clamps`: Values outside bounds are clamped to min/max.\n  Example: percent 150 → 100, percent -10 → 0\n\n- `Wraps`: Values wrap around using modular arithmetic.\n  Example: degrees 370 → 10, degrees -10 → 350\n\n- `Finite`: Values must be within bounds; out-of-bounds is invalid.\n  Used when clamping/wrapping would lose semantic meaning.\n  Example: array index must be valid, no \"clamping\" to last element\n\n## At Billion-Agent Scale\n\nAgents MUST know the behavior to correctly handle edge cases.\nWithout this, an agent cannot know if 361° should become 1° or 359°.\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"data","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[125,11],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[122,1]},"title":"BoundsBehavior"},{"children":[],"comments":"Documentation of valid bounds for a numeric type.\n\nThis is metadata - it describes what values are valid, for use in:\n- UI generation (sliders, input validation)\n- JSON schema generation\n- Documentation\n- Agent understanding\n\n## Fields\n\n- `min`: Minimum valid value (inclusive)\n- `max`: Maximum valid value (inclusive for Clamps/Finite, exclusive for Wraps)\n- `behavior`: How values outside bounds are handled\n- `name`: Short identifier for UI labels\n- `description`: Human-readable description for tooltips\n","info":{"arguments":[["a",null]],"declType":"typeSynonym","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Record"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["min",{"annotation":[],"contents":"a","tag":"TypeVar"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["max",{"annotation":[],"contents":"a","tag":"TypeVar"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["behavior",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Bounded"],"BoundsBehavior"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["name",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"String"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["description",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"String"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"tag":"REmpty"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[160,4],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[154,1]},"title":"Bounds"},{"children":[],"comments":"Integer bounds\n","info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"typeSynonym","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Bounded"],"Bounds"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[163,28],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[163,1]},"title":"IntBounds"},{"children":[],"comments":"Number bounds\n","info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"typeSynonym","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Bounded"],"Bounds"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[166,34],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[166,1]},"title":"NumberBounds"},{"children":[],"comments":"Create bounds documentation with explicit behavior.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":{"identifier":"a","kind":null,"skolem":null,"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":"a","tag":"TypeVar"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":"a","tag":"TypeVar"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Bounded"],"BoundsBehavior"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"String"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"String"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Bounded"],"Bounds"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":"a","tag":"TypeVar"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},"visibility":"TypeVarInvisible"},"tag":"ForAll"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[169,77],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[169,1]},"title":"bounds"},{"children":[],"comments":"Create integer bounds with explicit behavior.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Bounded"],"BoundsBehavior"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"String"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"String"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Bounded"],"IntBounds"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[179,75],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[179,1]},"title":"intBounds"},{"children":[],"comments":"Create number bounds with explicit behavior.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Bounded"],"BoundsBehavior"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"String"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"String"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Bounded"],"NumberBounds"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[183,87],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[183,1]},"title":"numberBounds"},{"children":[],"comments":"Clamp an integer to bounds\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[191,37],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[191,1]},"title":"clampInt"},{"children":[],"comments":"Clamp a number to bounds (NaN/Infinity-safe).\n\nIf the input is NaN or Infinity, returns minVal (safe fallback).\nThis prevents non-finite values from propagating through the system.\n\n## At Billion-Agent Scale\n\nNaN is the escape hatch for all bounds checks. A malicious actor\ncould craft `0.0 / 0.0` to bypass validation. This function closes\nthat vector by treating non-finite values as out-of-bounds.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[207,52],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[207,1]},"title":"clampNumber"},{"children":[],"comments":"Clamp a number to minimum only (no upper bound)\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[215,45],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[215,1]},"title":"clampNumberMin"},{"children":[],"comments":"Clamp a number to maximum only (no lower bound)\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[221,45],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[221,1]},"title":"clampNumberMax"},{"children":[],"comments":"Wrap an integer to bounds using modular arithmetic.\n\nThe range is [min, max), meaning max wraps to min.\n\n```purescript\nwrapInt 0 360 370   -- 10\nwrapInt 0 360 (-10) -- 350\nwrapInt 0 360 360   -- 0\n```\n\n## Mathematical Definition\n\nwrapInt min max n = min + ((n - min) `mod` (max - min))\n\nThis handles negative values correctly via PureScript's mod behavior.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[245,36],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[245,1]},"title":"wrapInt"},{"children":[],"comments":"Wrap a number to bounds using modular arithmetic (NaN/Infinity-safe).\n\nThe range is [min, max), meaning max wraps to min.\nIf input is NaN or Infinity, returns minVal (safe fallback).\n\n```purescript\nwrapNumber 0.0 360.0 370.0   -- 10.0\nwrapNumber 0.0 360.0 (-10.0) -- 350.0\nwrapNumber 0.0 1.0 1.5       -- 0.5\nwrapNumber 0.0 360.0 Infinity -- 0.0 (safe fallback)\n```\n\n## At Billion-Agent Scale\n\n`Infinity / range` produces Infinity, and `Infinity - Infinity` produces NaN.\nWithout this guard, Infinity input becomes NaN output, poisoning the system.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[270,51],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[270,1]},"title":"wrapNumber"},{"children":[],"comments":"Ensure a number is finite, returning fallback if not\n\nProtects against Infinity and NaN propagating through calculations:\n```purescript\nensureFinite (1.0 / 0.0) 0.0  -- 0.0 (Infinity replaced with fallback)\nensureFinite (0.0 / 0.0) 0.0  -- 0.0 (NaN replaced with fallback)\nensureFinite 42.0 0.0         -- 42.0 (finite, unchanged)\n```\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[312,43],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[312,1]},"title":"ensureFinite"},{"children":[],"comments":"Check if a number is finite (not Infinity, -Infinity, or NaN)\n\nUses the pattern that NaN /= NaN and comparison with Infinity.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Boolean"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[301,36],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[301,1]},"title":"isFiniteNumber"},{"children":[],"comments":"Require a number to be finite, returning Nothing for NaN/Infinity.\n\nThis is the **correct** approach for input validation:\n```purescript\nrequireFinite 42.0         -- Just 42.0\nrequireFinite (1.0 / 0.0)  -- Nothing (Infinity rejected)\nrequireFinite (0.0 / 0.0)  -- Nothing (NaN rejected)\n```\n\n## Security Model\n\nNaN and Infinity are **attack vectors**. A malicious actor crafting\n`0.0 / 0.0` or `1.0 / 0.0` can bypass bounds checks (NaN fails all\ncomparisons, Infinity exceeds all bounds but may slip through).\n\n**Rejecting** these values at the boundary is the only safe approach.\nSilent clamping masks the attack; rejection surfaces it.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Maybe"],"Maybe"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[334,40],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[334,1]},"title":"requireFinite"},{"children":[],"comments":"Reject non-finite numbers, returning an error message.\n\nFor APIs that need to report WHY a value was rejected:\n```purescript\nrejectNonFinite \"fps\" (1.0 / 0.0)  \n  -- Left \"fps: Infinity is not a valid finite number\"\n```\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"String"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Either"],"Either"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"String"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[346,60],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[346,1]},"title":"rejectNonFinite"},{"children":[],"comments":"Check if an integer is within bounds\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Boolean"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[287,44],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[287,1]},"title":"inBoundsInt"},{"children":[],"comments":"Check if a number is within bounds\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Boolean"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[291,56],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[291,1]},"title":"inBoundsNumber"},{"children":[],"comments":"Percentage bounds (0-100), clamps at limits.\n\n150% becomes 100%, -10% becomes 0%.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Bounded"],"IntBounds"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[359,21],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[359,1]},"title":"percent"},{"children":[],"comments":"Unit interval bounds (0.0-1.0), clamps at limits.\n\n1.5 becomes 1.0, -0.5 becomes 0.0.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Bounded"],"NumberBounds"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[365,21],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[365,1]},"title":"unit"},{"children":[],"comments":"Byte bounds (0-255), clamps at limits.\n\n300 becomes 255, -10 becomes 0.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Bounded"],"IntBounds"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[371,18],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[371,1]},"title":"byte"},{"children":[],"comments":"Degree bounds (0-360), WRAPS at limits.\n\n370° becomes 10°, -10° becomes 350°.\nRange is [0, 360) — 360 wraps to 0.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Bounded"],"IntBounds"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[378,21],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[378,1]},"title":"degrees"},{"children":[],"comments":"Normalized bounds (0.0-1.0), clamps at limits.\n\nAlias for unit, more descriptive in some contexts.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Bounded"],"NumberBounds"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[384,27],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[384,1]},"title":"normalized"},{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Bounded"],"UnitInterval"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[413,50],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[413,1]},"title":"eqUnitInterval"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Bounded"],"UnitInterval"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[414,52],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[414,1]},"title":"ordUnitInterval"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Bounded"],"UnitInterval"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[417,59],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Bounded.purs","start":[416,1]},"title":"showUnitInterval"}],"comments":"A number constrained to [0.0, 1.0].\n\nThis is the fundamental bounded numeric type for:\n- Probabilities and fractional selections\n- Opacity/alpha values\n- Interpolation parameters (t)\n- Normalized coordinates\n\n## Invariant\n\nThe wrapped value is ALWAYS in [0.0, 1.0]. This is enforced by:\n- Smart constructor `unitInterval` returns Maybe\n- Clamping constructor `clampUnit` always succeeds\n- All operations preserve the invariant\n\n## At Billion-Agent Scale\n\nWhen agents communicate fractional solutions, using `UnitInterval`\nguarantees the receiving agent wi